# ============================================
# DREC PMS - Environment Variables
# ============================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the actual values.
# NEVER commit the real .env file to version control!

# Database (Neon PostgreSQL)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@ep-xxx.region.aws.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require

# Application
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000

# NextAuth
NEXTAUTH_URL=https://your-domain.railway.app
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your-random-secret-key-here
Analyze the repository at https://github.com/JohnzzzAntony/new-.git to prepare it for deployment on Railway.app via GitHub. Provide a comprehensive guide that includes all necessary configuration files (such as a Dockerfile, railway.json, or language-specific dependency files), a list of all required environment variables, and step-by-step instructions to ensure a successful deployment